text.section:
The State Board of Education shall:
Disburse all funds provided, and administer all programs established under this subtitle, for the rehabilitation of disabled individuals;
Appoint and fix the compensation of the personnel necessary to administer this subtitle;
Rehabilitate and place in gainful occupations individuals eligible for the benefits of this subtitle;
Rehabilitate eligible individuals to function more independently;
Adopt rules and regulations necessary to administer this subtitle;
Report annually to the Governor on the administration of this subtitle; and
Cooperate with other public and private departments, agencies, and institutions to:
Provide for the rehabilitation of disabled individuals;
Provide for the independent living rehabilitation of severely disabled individuals;
Study the problems of rehabilitation; and
Develop and provide programs, facilities, and services necessary or desirable to implement this subtitle.
